theorem Topology.interior_compl_eq_compl_closure {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    (A : Set X) : interior ((A : Set X)·∂ú) = (closure (A : Set X))·∂ú := by
  ext x
  constructor
  ¬∑ intro hx
    -- `x` lies in an open neighbourhood contained in `A·∂ú`
    have hnhds : (interior (A·∂ú) : Set X) ‚àà ùìù x :=
      (isOpen_interior.mem_nhds hx)
    -- If `x` were also in `closure A`, every neighbourhood of `x` would meet `A`,
    -- contradicting the fact that `interior (A·∂ú)` is disjoint from `A`.
    have hcontra : x ‚àà closure (A : Set X) ‚Üí False := by
      intro hxcl
      have h := (mem_closure_iff).1 hxcl _ isOpen_interior hnhds
      simpa [interior_subset] using h
    exact by
      -- `x` cannot be in `closure A`
      simpa [Set.mem_compl] using not_exists.mpr hcontra
  ¬∑ intro hx
    -- Work with the open set `U = (closure A)·∂ú` containing `x`.
    set U : Set X := (closure (A : Set X))·∂ú with hUdef
    have hU_open : IsOpen U := isClosed_closure.isOpen_compl
    have hxU : x ‚àà U := by
      simpa [hUdef, Set.mem_compl] using hx
    -- Since `A ‚äÜ closure A`, we have `U ‚äÜ A·∂ú`.
    have hU_subset : (U : Set X) ‚äÜ (A : Set X)·∂ú := by
      intro y hy
      by_contra hAy
      have : (y : X) ‚àà closure (A : Set X) := subset_closure hAy
      have : y ‚àà U := hy
      simpa [hUdef, Set.mem_compl] using And.intro this this
    -- `U` is an open subset of `A·∂ú`, hence contained in its interior.
    have hU_interior : (U : Set X) ‚äÜ interior (A·∂ú) :=
      interior_maximal hU_subset hU_open
    exact hU_interior hxU
